e^{ix}
e^{ix}=\cos(x)+i\sin(x)
 \begin{align*} \int \sin(x)dx &= \int Im(e^{ix})dx = Im\left(\int e^{ix}dx\right)= Im\left(\frac{1}{i}e^{ix}+c\right) = Im\left(-ie^{ix}+c\right) \\ &= Im(-i[\cos(x)+i\sin(x)]+c) = Im(-i[\cos(x)+i\sin(x)]+c) \\ &= Im(-i\cos(x)+\sin(x)+c) = -\cos(x) + c \end{align*} 
